Create directory for the packages
mkdir ~/Rpkg

Create in $HOME
1) .Rprofile 
2) .Renviron
see samples

.Rprofile
will need to install packages prior to adding them to startup
* No .Renviron 
  install.packages("pgmm", lib = "$HOME/Rpkg")
 * with .Renviron
   install.packages("pgmm")
   
 .Renviron
 to check, in R do:
 > .libPaths()
 [1] "/home/taitpa/Rpkg"                                                                                  
[2] "/cvmfs/soft.computecanada.ca/easybuild/software/2017/avx512/Compiler/gcc7.3/r/3.5.2/lib64/R/library"

Copy to your machine
rsync --progress -avzhe "ssh -i $HOME/.ssh/id_yeats1_2019-02-19" taitpa@yeats.sharcnet.ca:~/.Renviron ~


clustermq.template 
  * configures slurm to properly interface with clustermq